.*****************************************************************
.*  Primary help text for the command.
.*****************************************************************
:HELP NAME='RUNCLSTM'.
Run CL Statements - Help
:P.
RUNCLSTM can be used to excute CL statements from a CL Script
member. Just put the CL statements that are to be executed
into a source member and run RUNCLSTM against the member.
:P.
Beside CL statements RUNCLSTM can also execute embedded SQL
statements.
:P.
Although the command originally was designed to help us to
customize a change management product RUNCLSTM can also be used
stand alone.
:P.
The following tags are supported by RUNCLSTM:
:P.
:PARML.
:PT./EXEC SQL
:PD.This tag marks the beginning of an embedded SQL section. Actually
this tag switches RUNCLSTM into SQL mode. In contrast to the SQL syntax
RUNCLSTM needs the typical CL continuation character '+' or '-' to
identify a continuation line. Also the ';' character as an End-Of-Line
marker must not be specified.

:PT./END-EXEC
:PD.This Tag marks the end of a SQL section.
:EPARML.
:P.
:HP3.Attention::EHP3.
:P.
The CL statement :HP2.MONMSG:EHP2. is not fully supported. The keywords
CMPDTA and EXEC are not supported.
:P.
MONMSG *can* be used to monitor SQL errors!
:P.
MONMSG can also be used to monitor generic messages like CPF9800 or
CPF0000.
:P.
Global error monitoring is not supported.

:P.
Example:
:P.
:LINES.
0001.00
0002.00  /EXEC SQL
0003.00         DROP   TABLE &LI/MYFILE
0004.00         MONMSG     MSGID(SQL0204)
0005.00
0006.00         CREATE TABLE &LI/MYFILE +
0007.00                (FLD1    CHAR (30) NOT NULL WITH DEFAULT, +
0008.00                 FLD2    CHAR (30) NOT NULL WITH DEFAULT)
0009.00  /END-EXEC
0010.00
0011.00  DLTCMD     CMD(&LI/MYCMD)
0012.00  MONMSG     MSGID(CPF2105)
0013.00
:ELINES.
:EHELP.

.*****************************************************************
.*  Help text for the command parameters.
.*****************************************************************

.********************************************
.*  Keyword:  FILE
.********************************************
:HELP NAME='RUNCLSTM/USESRCFILE'.
Source file (USESRCFILE) - Help
:XH3.Use source file (USESRCFILE)
:P.
Specifies the qualified name of the source file that contains the SQL
statements to be run.

:IMHELP name='COM/REQPARM'.
:P.
The name of the source file can be qualified by one of the following
library values:

:PARML.
:PT.:PK DEF.*LIBL:EPK.
:PD.All libraries in the job's library list are searched
until the first match is found.

:PT.:PV.*CURLIB:EPV.
:PD.The current library for the job is searched.  If no
library is specified as the current library for the
job, the QGPL library is used.

:PT.:PV.library-name:EPV.
:PD.Specify the name of the library to be searched.
:EPARML.

:IMHELP name='COM/VALUES'.

:PARML.
:PT.:PV.source-file-name:EPV.
:PD.Specify the name of the source file that contains the
SQL statements to be run.  The source file can be a
database file or an inline data file.
:EPARML.

:EHELP.

